CAPE TOWN An ambulance with a patient on board was stuck in Meiringspoort pass, between De Rust and Beaufort West, after heavy rains caused roads to flood.Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa said the ambulance and a passenger bus were removed early Monday morning. The ambulance had a patient on board, picked up from one of the nearby farms."He was eventually transported to a hospital once the flooding had subsided, said Africa.Africa said the roads are still closed due to the flooding but relevant emergency personnel are still at the scene.eNCA